description:
TPO 16/92 - T3 (5) (hornbeam) - cut back to approximatley achieve a 1.5m clearance from building and remove large dead section;
T2 (6) and T1 (7) (hornbeam) - cut back to approximatley achieve a 1.5m clearance from building and reduce spread on Ridings side back to previous points;
T7 (11) (oak) - cut back to approximatley achieve a 2.5m clearance from building;
G3 (12 and 14) (lime) - cut back to approximatley achieve a 2.5m clearance from building, sever ivy and de-sucker to approximatley 3m;
G3 (13) (lime) - sever ivy and de-sucker to approximatley 3m;
G2 (19) (oak) - cut back to achieve a 2m clearance from building, crown lift 5m over lane and sever ivy;
G2 (21, 22 and 23) (sycamore) - crown lift approximatley 5m over lane and cut back off building to approximatley achieve a 2m clearance;
G2 (24) oak - sever ivy, crown lift approximatley 5m over lane and cut back off building to approximatley achieve a 2m clearance;
G2 (26 and 27) (sycamore) - sever ivy;
T3 (29) (oak) - remove dead limb towards T20, reduce crown by approximatley 2 - 3m;
G1 (36) (hornbeam) - cut back from building to approximatley 3m;
T5 (38) (lime) - re-pollard at 8m (pending fell); and
T4 (39) (lime) - cut back overhang to approximatley achieve a 2m clearance from building.
